Part 3: Ubuntu Client Configuration
Step 3.1: Configure PC1 (Behind FW1 - IP: 10.10.10.2)
Open Terminal on Ubuntu PC1:

text
1. Press Ctrl+Alt+T to open terminal
2. Check current IP address:
   ip addr show
3. Add route to remote network:
   sudo ip route add 10.20.0.0/24 via 10.10.10.1
4. Verify route was added:
   ip route show
Expected output:

text
default via 10.10.10.1 dev eth0
10.10.10.0/24 dev eth0 proto kernel scope link src 10.10.10.2
10.20.0.0/24 via 10.10.10.1 dev eth0
To make route permanent (Netplan method):

text
1. Find netplan config file:
   ls /etc/netplan/
   (example: 01-netcfg.yaml or 00-installer-config.yaml)

2. Edit the file:
   sudo nano /etc/netplan/01-netcfg.yaml

3. Add routes section under your interface:
yaml
network:
  version: 2
  renderer: networkd
  ethernets:
    eth0:
      addresses:
        - 10.10.10.2/24
      gateway4: 10.10.10.1
      nameservers:
        addresses: [8.8.8.8, 8.8.4.4]
      routes:
        - to: 10.20.0.0/24
          via: 10.10.10.1
text
4. Save file (Ctrl+X, then Y, then Enter)
5. Apply configuration:
   sudo netplan apply
