text
default via 10.20.0.1 dev eth0
10.10.10.0/24 via 10.20.0.1 dev eth0
10.20.0.0/24 dev eth0 proto kernel scope link src 10.20.0.2
To make route permanent (Netplan method):

text
1. Edit netplan config:
   sudo nano /etc/netplan/01-netcfg.yaml

2. Add routes section:
yaml
network:
  version: 2
  renderer: networkd
  ethernets:
    eth0:
      addresses:
        - 10.20.0.2/24
      gateway4: 10.20.0.1
      nameservers:
        addresses: [8.8.8.8, 8.8.4.4]
      routes:
        - to: 10.10.10.0/24
          via: 10.20.0.1
text
3. Save and apply:
   sudo netplan apply
Step 3.3: Disable Ubuntu Firewall (for testing only)
If ping fails, temporarily disable UFW:

text
# Check status
sudo ufw status

# Disable for testing
sudo ufw disable

# Test ping again
ping 10.20.0.2 (from PC1) or ping 10.10.10.2 (from PC2)

# Re-enable after testing
sudo ufw enable

# Or allow ICMP through firewall
sudo ufw allow proto icmp from 10.10.10.0/24 to any
